    "text_instructions": [
      {
        "id": "00000000000000000000000000000012",
        "content": [
          "## General Instructions\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "1. This Genie has a 2 data sources: primary main.etoro_kpi_stg.vw_raf_for_genie2. All queries must use this view.\r\n",
          "and secondary the main.etoro_kpi_stg.vw_raf_config_for_genie\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "2. One row = one referral pair. Each row represents a unique referrer-referred relationship. The grain is (ReferringCID, ReferredCID).\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "3. All monetary values are in USD. ReferringCompensationAmount, ReferredCompensationAmount, RealizedEquity, and TotalInvestedAmount are all in USD. No conversion needed.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "4. Not every referral results in a reward. Only rows with RafStatusName = 'RafGiven' represent successful referrals where compensation was granted (~93% of records). The remaining ~7% failed for various reasons.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "5. RafStatusName can be composite. A single row may have multiple failure reasons separated by commas (e.g. 'FTDReferredCheckAmount, RegistrationDateExpired'). Use LIKE '%reason%' to check for a specific reason.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "6. This view enriches referrer attributes only. Customer dimensions (Country, Regulation, PlayerLevel, GuruStatus) come from the referrer (inviter), not the referred friend.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "7. When counting referrers, use COUNT(DISTINCT ReferringCID). A single referrer can have multiple referrals.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "8. When counting referred friends, use COUNT(DISTINCT ReferredCID).\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "9. Date filtering: use CompensationDate for when rewards were paid or ProcessingDate for when the referral was processed. Both are TIMESTAMP columns. Use DATE() to extract the date portion.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "10. FraudReason is sparse (NULL for ~99.6%). Only filter on it when explicitly asked about fraud details.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "11. IsProcessed = 1 means fully processed. IsProcessed = 0 means pending.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "12. Club tier hierarchy: Bronze < Silver < Gold < Platinum < Platinum Plus < Diamond. PlayerLevelName = 'Internal' is system-level.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "13. IsPI is a binary flag (0/1). For the specific PI tier, use GuruStatusName. Value 'No' means not a Popular Investor.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "14. RealizedEquity columns reflect the CURRENT balance snapshot in USD. Not historical.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "15. TotalInvestedAmount columns reflect yesterday's AUM snapshot in USD. NULL means no AUM record yesterday.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "16. CID and GCID are unique ID's of the customer. present them as number without commas. present GCID only if asked\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "17. dont include in you calculation any raf that was processed before  2023-06-05\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "## Business Context\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "eToro is a global multi-asset trading and investment platform. Customers trade stocks, crypto, indices, currencies, commodities, and ETFs.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "The Refer-a-Friend (RAF) program incentivizes existing customers (referrers) to invite new users (referees/friends) to join the platform. When a referred friend meets qualification criteria, the referrer may receive a reward.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "A referral does NOT automatically result in a reward. The referee must complete qualifying actions (registration, KYC, first deposit, minimum trading) before the referrer becomes eligible. Referrals that do not meet criteria remain unrewarded.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Qualification criteria may vary by campaign, regulation, or region and can include: account registration, identity verification (KYC), first-time deposit (FTD) above a minimum threshold, and minimum trading volume.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Rewards may be monetary (cash credit, bonus) or non-monetary (trading credits, fee discounts). Amounts vary by campaign and region.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "RAF rules differ across regulatory jurisdictions (CySEC for EU, FCA for UK, ASIC for Australia, FSRA for UAE, FSA Seychelles)."
        ]
      }
    ],
    "example_question_sqls": [
      {
        "id": "00000000000000000000000000000013",
        "question": [
          "RAF Overview - Referral counts by status"
        ],
        "sql": [
          "SELECT RafStatusName, COUNT(*) AS ReferralCount, ROUND(COUNT(*) * 100.0 / SUM(COUNT(*)) OVER (), 2) AS PctOfTotal FROM main.etoro_kpi_stg.vw_raf_for_genie GROUP BY RafStatusName ORDER BY ReferralCount DESC"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "00000000000000000000000000000014",
        "question": [
          "Monthly successful referrals and total compensation for 2025"
        ],
        "sql": [
          "SELECT DATE_FORMAT(CompensationDate, 'yyyy-MM') AS CompensationMonth, COUNT(*) AS SuccessfulReferrals, COUNT(DISTINCT ReferringCID) AS UniqueReferrers, COUNT(DISTINCT ReferredCID) AS UniqueReferred, SUM(ReferringCompensationAmount) AS TotalReferrerRewardUSD, SUM(ReferredCompensationAmount) AS TotalReferredRewardUSD FROM main.etoro_kpi_stg.vw_raf_for_genie WHERE RafStatusName = 'RafGiven' AND YEAR(CompensationDate) = 2025 GROUP BY DATE_FORMAT(CompensationDate, 'yyyy-MM') ORDER BY CompensationMonth"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "00000000000000000000000000000015",
        "question": [
          "Top 20 referrers by number of successful referrals"
        ],
        "sql": [
          "SELECT ReferringCID, Country, PlayerLevelName, RegulationName, COUNT(*) AS SuccessfulReferrals, SUM(ReferringCompensationAmount) AS TotalRewardUSD FROM main.etoro_kpi_stg.vw_raf_for_genie WHERE RafStatusName = 'RafGiven' GROUP BY ReferringCID, Country, PlayerLevelName, RegulationName ORDER BY SuccessfulReferrals DESC LIMIT 20"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "00000000000000000000000000000016",
        "question": [
          "Referral conversion rate by country"
        ],
        "sql": [
          "SELECT Country, COUNT(*) AS TotalReferrals, COUNT(CASE WHEN RafStatusName = 'RafGiven' THEN 1 END) AS SuccessfulReferrals, ROUND(COUNT(CASE WHEN RafStatusName = 'RafGiven' THEN 1 END) * 100.0 / COUNT(*), 2) AS ConversionRatePct FROM main.etoro_kpi_stg.vw_raf_for_genie GROUP BY Country HAVING COUNT(*) >= 10 ORDER BY ConversionRatePct DESC"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "00000000000000000000000000000017",
        "question": [
          "Failure reason breakdown excluding successful referrals"
        ],
        "sql": [
          "SELECT RafStatusName, COUNT(*) AS FailureCount, ROUND(COUNT(*) * 100.0 / SUM(COUNT(*)) OVER (), 2) AS PctOfFailures FROM main.etoro_kpi_stg.vw_raf_for_genie WHERE RafStatusName != 'RafGiven' GROUP BY RafStatusName ORDER BY FailureCount DESC"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "00000000000000000000000000000018",
        "question": [
          "Compensation by club tier"
        ],
        "sql": [
          "SELECT PlayerLevelName, COUNT(*) AS TotalReferrals, COUNT(CASE WHEN RafStatusName = 'RafGiven' THEN 1 END) AS SuccessfulReferrals, SUM(COALESCE(ReferringCompensationAmount, 0)) AS TotalReferrerRewardUSD, AVG(CASE WHEN RafStatusName = 'RafGiven' THEN ReferringCompensationAmount END) AS AvgRewardUSD FROM main.etoro_kpi_stg.vw_raf_for_genie GROUP BY PlayerLevelName ORDER BY TotalReferrals DESC"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "00000000000000000000000000000019",
        "question": [
          "Fraud analysis by country and regulation"
        ],
        "sql": [
          "SELECT Country, RegulationName, COUNT(*) AS FraudCases, COUNT(DISTINCT ReferringCID) AS FraudReferrers FROM main.etoro_kpi_stg.vw_raf_for_genie WHERE RafStatusName LIKE '%Fraud%' GROUP BY Country, RegulationName ORDER BY FraudCases DESC"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "0000000000000000000000000000001a",
        "question": [
          "Popular Investor vs regular customer referral activity"
        ],
        "sql": [
          "SELECT CASE WHEN IsPI = 1 THEN 'Popular Investor' ELSE 'Regular Customer' END AS ReferrerType, COUNT(*) AS TotalReferrals, COUNT(CASE WHEN RafStatusName = 'RafGiven' THEN 1 END) AS SuccessfulReferrals, ROUND(COUNT(CASE WHEN RafStatusName = 'RafGiven' THEN 1 END) * 100.0 / COUNT(*), 2) AS ConversionRatePct, SUM(COALESCE(ReferringCompensationAmount, 0)) AS TotalRewardUSD FROM main.etoro_kpi_stg.vw_raf_for_genie GROUP BY CASE WHEN IsPI = 1 THEN 'Popular Investor' ELSE 'Regular Customer' END"
        ]
      }
    ],
